## Python Style Guide

### PEP 8 Compliance
- Indentation: 4 spaces
- Line length: 88 characters
- Encoding: UTF-8
- Imports: Grouped (standard, third-party, local)

## Naming Conventions

### Variables and Functions
```python
# Good
user_data = {}
def process_data(): pass

# Bad
userData = {}  # camelCase
```

### Classes
```python
# Good
class DataProcessor: pass

# Bad
class data_processor: pass  # snake_case
```

### Constants
```python
# Good
MAX_RETRIES = 3
DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 30

# Bad
maxRetries = 3  # camelCase
```

